<section class="section about-section" id="about">
  <div class="container about-inner">
    <div class="about-img-wrap">
      <img
        src="/images/Headshot.jpeg"
        alt="Jacob Gordon — JG Concrete"
        class="about-headshot"
      />
      <div class="about-credential">
        <img
          src="/images/CMI_Icon.png"
          alt="Concrete Industry Management — Texas State University"
          class="cim-logo"
        />
        <span>CIM Graduate — Texas State</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="about-text">
      <h2>Hi, I'm Jacob</h2>
      <p>
        I'm a concrete contractor based in East Dallas, and concrete has been a part of my life
        for as long as I can remember. I grew up around the trade, watching family members work,
        learning the basics early, and developing a real respect for the craft. That background
        eventually led me to the Concrete Industry Management program at Texas State University,
        where I learned the technical side of concrete — mix design, materials testing, quality
        control, and how to build work that lasts. Combining what I learned at home with what I
        learned in the CIM program shaped the way I approach every project today.
      </p>
      <p>
        Along with my education, I've built hands-on experience completing patios, driveways,
        walkways, small slabs, and repair work throughout the Dallas area. I take pride in showing
        up, communicating clearly, and treating every project like it's going in my own yard.
        I'm growing my portfolio one job at a time, focusing on clean finishes, solid prep, and
        dependable results. When you hire me, you're getting someone who genuinely cares about
        the work and the people he's building for.
      </p>
      <a href="#quote" class="btn btn-primary">Get a Free Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
